headline: State Street (STT) Earnings Surge 60.5%, Reinforcing Bullish Profitability Narrative
summary: State Street (STT) posted a 60.5% jump in earnings over the past year, marking a significant turnaround from its five-year track record of a 0.8% annual decline. Net profit margin improved to 19.8% compared to 13.7% last year, and the share price now trades at $111.37. With future earnings expected to grow at 9.1% per year, investors will note profitability improvements even as forecasted growth lags behind the broader US market.
